sec.p:
Carrier recombination dynamics play a decisive role in emission behavior. We firstly investigate the excitation-density-dependent PL intensity for determining the carrier recombination types. The initial PL intensity (IPL) shows a quadratic dependence of excited carrier density for the films of Cs/Pb = 1.56 and Cs/Pb = 1.24 (Supplementary Fig. 6), which indicates the radiative recombination process is bimolecular. Meanwhile, by fitting the Arrhenius equation, the exciton binding energies of Cs/Pb = 1.56 and Cs/Pb = 1.24 are derived to be 48.7 and 41.6 meV, respectively (Supplementary Fig. 7)24,37. The relatively small exciton binding energies close to the room-temperature thermal energy indicate the dominant recombination mechanism is free-carriers39. Thereby, the radiative efficiency η\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
